OL,3,CGuernsey official heavily criticises
OL,4,CAurigny's summer service
OL,6,F"I will not hold back in expressing my
OL,7,Fconcern and making sure that this has
OL,8,Fto be solved very, very quickly
OL,9,Findeed."
OL,11,FDeputy Roffey also apologises to
OL,12,Fcustomers who were on the flight,
OL,13,Fsaying that it "shouldn't have
OL,14,Fhappened" and it was a "one-off".
OL,16,FWhile Deputy Roffey says he is
OL,17,Fconfident in the future of Guernsey's
OL,18,Fair links, he admits that the summer
OL,19,Fservice has not been acceptable.
