OL,3,CGuernsey official heavily criticises
OL,4,CAurigny's summer service
OL,6,FHe explains: "To be fair to Aurigny,
OL,7,Fthey have suffered the most incredible
OL,8,Fseries of unfortunate events.
OL,10,F"But that's something that they need
OL,11,Fto take into account and it's on their
OL,12,Fhead that tickets they sell can be
OL,13,Fhonoured.
OL,15,F"It 'cuts no ice' and 'butters no
OL,16,Fparsnips' for businessmen who haven't
OL,17,Fbeen able to get over for conferences
OL,18,Fand people who have been on holiday
OL,19,Fand then get stuck for a day or two in
OL,20,FGatwick."
